    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/how-gen-ai-can-supercharge-the-quality-of-your-erp-migration/qaq-p/13955512</id>
    <title>How Gen AI can supercharge the quality of your ERP migration</title>
    <updated>2024-12-04T15:33:38.344000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Jeba_Abraham</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/1874723</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Our research&lt;A href="#_ftn1" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow noreferrer"&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;[1]&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/A&gt; shows that over 93% of organizations that haven’t upgraded to SAP S/4HANA have already started or plan to migrate within the next 24 months. Yet these organizations will naturally face a number of transitional challenges – ranging from security risks and lack of in-house expertise to customer dissatisfaction and possible financial impact. In order to succeed, organizations must implement robust continuous testing methods that will minimize this risk and deliver uninterrupted business outcomes, while managing the additional changes and updates demanded after the transition. Technology will inevitably play a critical role in executing this strategy effectively, and the rise of new technologies - like Generative AI - must be embraced in future approaches. Read more on how GenAI can aid this transformation here&amp;nbsp;&lt;A title="https://bit.ly/3YTE1OH" href="https://bit.ly/3YTE1OH" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow noreferrer"&gt;https://bit.ly/3YTE1OH&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;A href="#_ftnref1" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow noreferrer"&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;[1]&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/A&gt; State of Worldwide Business Assurance for SAP Solutions 2023&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/how-gen-ai-can-supercharge-the-quality-of-your-erp-migration/qaq-p/13955512"/>
    <published>2024-12-04T15:33:38.344000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
